.head 2 -  Description: This logs on to the remote FTP site and checks for any files to action.
	As per Bunnings specifications, only files with a GZIP extention are scanned for.
	If any are found, they are moved to a temporary location and then downloaded to the local machine.
	
The local machine is then checked for any files to transmitted to the remote site.
	If any are found, they are copied to the remote location where they are renamed to conform to the Bunning specification.
	
